## Plan Summary

**Only `common/chat.cpp` is modified** — two additions, zero deletions.

---

### Change 1 — New handler function  
**Insert after line 1517** (after `common_chat_params_init_gigachat_v3`'s closing `}`), **before `namespace workaround {`**:

```cpp
static common_chat_params common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(
        const common_chat_template & /* tmpl */,
        const autoparser::generation_params & inputs) {

    common_chat_params data;

    std::string system_prompt;
    std::string prompt;
    bool first_user = true;

    for (const auto & msg : inputs.messages) {
        auto role    = msg.value("role", "");
        auto content = msg.value("content", "");

        if (role == "system") {
            system_prompt = content;
        } else if (role == "user") {
            std::string turn_content;
            if (first_user && !system_prompt.empty()) {
                turn_content = system_prompt + "\n" + content;
                first_user = false;
            } else {
                turn_content = content;
                first_user = false;
            }
            prompt += "[INST] " + turn_content + " [/INST]";
        } else if (role == "assistant") {
            prompt += " " + content + "</s>";
        }
    }

    data.prompt = prompt;
    data.format = COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_CONTENT_ONLY;
    return data;
}
```

