### Change 2 — Detection block  
**Insert after line 1688** (after GigaChatV3 dispatch), **before `return std::nullopt;`**:

```cpp
    // Mistral Instruct v0.3 - [INST]/[/INST] without [SYSTEM_PROMPT]
    if (src.find("[INST]") != std::string::npos &&
        src.find("[/INST]") != std::string::npos &&
        src.find("[SYSTEM_PROMPT]") == std::string::npos) {
        LOG_DBG("Using specialized template: Mistral Instruct v3\n");
        return common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(tmpl, params);
    }
```

---

### Key design decisions
- **No Jinja execution** — the handler builds the prompt directly from `inputs.messages`, so `tmpl` is marked unused
- **System message handling** — captured and prepended to the first user turn with `\n`; omitted if absent
- **`COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_CONTENT_ONLY`** — correct since this format has no tool-call PEG parsing
- **Detection safety** — `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` absence ensures Ministral 3 templates (which also use `[INST]`) are never incorrectly matched by this new handler
